The Smith & Wesson Model 10, previously known as the Smith & Wesson Military & Police or the Smith & Wesson Victory Model, is a .38-caliber revolver developed from the Smith & Wesson .38 Hand Ejector Model of 1889. In production since 1899, it is a fixed-sight, six-shot handgun with a fluted cylinder. Over its long production run it has been available with barrel lengths of 2 in (51 mm), 3 in (76 mm), 4 in (100 mm), 5 in (130 mm), and 6 in (150 mm). Barrels of 2.5 inches (64 mm) are also known to have been made for special contracts. AUGUST AND SEPTEMBER CLASSES ARE FILLING FAST!

title: For Sale/Trade:  CMMG 16" M4 22 Barrel w/ SS Collar for Dedicated Upper
postcontent:
This is a very lightly used CMMG 16" M4 .22 Barrel w/ Stainless Steel Collar, drilled for A2 front sight base pins. I have put about 300 rounds down this barrel and have had very good accuracy. 

If you have a 22 conversion kit from CMMG, use this barrel to build your dedicated upper. From what I have read, your typical 5.56/223 barrel has an inside diameter of .224 inches, 22LR best performs with a .222 inch barrel, thus you will get much better performance from a dedicated upper with this barrel (I.D. .222") than with using your 223. And not to mention you don't run the risk of clogging up your chamber or gas chamber with 22lr soot. 

I am getting rid of this simply because it is not being used and it just sits in my safe. The barrel and SS collar run $160 from CMMG plus shipping. I am offering this deal for $120 and with potential to be cheaper (read ahead) 

Potential trade: If you have the 223 conversion kit with the chamber adapter for 223/5.56 and you are upgrading to a dedicated upper. Throw in your chamber adapter (that looks like a 223 case sticking out the front) and I will give you a fair discount (depending on the material of the chamber adapter - i.e. stainless or parkerized). 

Here is some info from CMMG's website: Convert your 22-ARC into a dedicated upper! Add an upper receiver and replace your chamber adapter with the barrel adapter collar and you have a dedicated .22 LR upper. 16" barrel. 1/2x28 threaded muzzle. Stanless Steel dedicated chamber adapter with ball detent*.
